title: Man Utd transfer news: Wayne Rooney to China is 'madness' – Roy Keane | Metro News
text:
George Bellshaw for Metro.co.uk Thursday 23 Feb 2017 10:18 am 
Roy Keane has slammed talk of Wayne Rooney going to China as ‘madness’ and believes he could still play at the top level anywhere in Europe. 
The Manchester United and England captain has been heavily linked with a move away from Old Trafford, with his agent believed to have jetted out to the Far East in order to secure a mega-money move. 
But former Red Devil Keane can’t fathom why Rooney wouldn’t want to extend his career at the top level in Europe. 
‘There’s no way Wayne Rooney should be going to China,’ he told ITV. 
‘He can still play football at the top level in England, Germany, Spain, Italy – madness. Will Rooney move to China? (Picture: Getty) 
When asked if he could still play for a big club outside of England, Keane replied: ‘Without a shadow of a doubt. 
‘Going to China – madness. He’s 31 years of age. There’s plenty left for Wayne Rooney to do in Europe. 
‘I don’t think he’s short of money, is he?’
